The '''Bicycle Industry''' or '''Cycling Industry''' can broadly be defined as the [[industry]] concerned with [[bicycles]] and [[cycling]]. It includes at least [[List of bicycle manufacturers|bicycle manufacturers]], part or component manufacturers, and accessory manufacturers. It can also include [[Distribution (business)|distributors]], [[Retailing|retailers]], bicycle organizations, bicycle event promoters, and bicycle related service providers.
The Global Bicycle Industry generales sales for over $45 bn in 2017 and is forecasted, according to analist consensus, at 6-0% p.a. over the next 5yr <ref>http://www.bike-eu.com/sales-trends/nieuws/2017/6/cycling-sales-to-grow-by-38-to-56-billion-euros-in-2024-10130327</ref>
In 2016 in the United States, it generated $6 billion of revenue <ref>https://www.statista.com/topics/1686/cycling</ref> and in Europe, it generated €14 bn in revenues.<ref>http://www.bike-eu.com/sales-trends/nieuws/2017/6/cycling-sales-to-grow-by-38-to-56-billion-euros-in-2024-10130327</ref>
